                            <comment id="51765" author="rweneck" created="Fri, 5 Mar 2010 00:59:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to achieve this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73958" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Fri, 16 Dec 2011 13:23:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Path variables are actually looked up in a Map&amp;lt;String, String&amp;gt; saved as a request attribute (HandlerMapping.URI_TEMPLATE_VARIABLES_ATTRIBUTE) by the DefaultAnnotationHandlerMapping (or the RequestMappingHandlerMapping in Spring 3.1). Since the RequestMappingHandlerMapping already has a setUrlDecode(boolean) property, it should know whether URI variables are decoded or not and has the possibility to decode them before preparing the map. Then you only need to set the urlDecode property only once. Do you see any reason why this shouldn&apos;t be done whenever urlDecode=false?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="73959" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Fri, 16 Dec 2011 13:25:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Assigning tentatively for resolution in 3.2 also modifying the title (was: &quot;Add decodePathVariable option to AnnotationMethodHandlerAdapter&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="78959" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Thu, 17 May 2012 13:40:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving this as duplicate even though it was opened earlier since &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-9098&quot; title=&quot;Decode URI variable values when UrlPathHelper.setUrlDecode() is set to false &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-9098&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-9098&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; happened to be fixed first.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
